## 0.2.0 — unreleased — M11 posture lift

[Change] M11 P3 — Sonnet 4.6 bundle-summary render in bl_bundle_build (src/bl.d/42-observe-router.sh) wrapping the deterministic summary.md generator with a bl_messages_call(claude-sonnet-4-6) path; --no-llm-summary flag + BL_DISABLE_LLM=1 env bypass cover test/cost-control modes; deterministic _bl_obs_render_summary_deterministic helper preserved at file scope as fallback on any Sonnet failure (auth/5xx/429), missing prompts/bundle-summary-system.md, or bypass trigger
[New] M11 P3 — prompts/bundle-summary-system.md: Sonnet system prompt for the summary.md render (≤2KB output budget; required sections: trigger/hypothesis, top-line findings, jump points, attention-worthy; treats embedded log content as untrusted)
[Change] M11 P4 — Haiku 4.5 FP-gate adjudication: src/bl.d/82-defend.sh _bl_defend_sig_fp_gate calls bl_messages_call(claude-haiku-4-5) after binary scan with ≤5 corpus samples spot-checked; fail-closed on verdict:match / parse error / unreachable; BL_DISABLE_LLM=1 bypass for tests + cost-control; new prompts/fp-gate-haiku-system.md authored as conservative adjudicator system prompt
[New] M11 P2 — src/bl.d/22-models.sh: bl_messages_call wrapper for Messages API (POST /v1/messages); 4-retry exponential backoff; foundation for Sonnet 4.6 (bundle summary) + Haiku 4.5 (FP-gate adjudication) routing
[Change] M11 P6 — bl_poll_pending real GET-poll loop (src/bl.d/20-api.sh): seen-set dedup, --timeout / --interval flags, end_turn proxy via 3-empty-cycles, BL_POLL_DRY_RUN=1 bypass; replaces single-cycle skeleton from M1
[New] M11 P6 — tests/03-poll.bats: 7 tests covering timeout, emit, dedup, end-of-pending, auth-fail propagation, dry-run, missing-case-id
[New] M11 P9 — five highest-leverage negative tests (preflight 401-auth-fail / consult schema-reject / defend yara fp_gate_trip / clean dry-run-receipt-expired + concurrent flock atomicity / setup partial-state recovery) — closes audit gap "228 tests, 70% smoke"; 234/234 green on debian12 + rocky9
[New] M11 P11 — exhibits/fleet-01/host-2-polyshell/ APSB25-94 fixture beef-up (50K-line Apache CLF + ~3K-line ModSec A/B/F/H/Z + 500-record journalctl JSON; deterministic seed=42 via scripts/synthesize-fixture-logs.sh; public Adobe advisory IOC patterns + RFC 5737 IPs only; lifts host-2 fixture bundle to ~100K tokens, exercises 1M-context curator defense)
[Change] M11 P1 — doc reconciliation: README skills count 48/13 → 65/20; "Try it" walkthrough flag spelling corrected (bl observe log apache --around / bl observe fs --mtime-since); README adaptive-thinking caveat (model-internal on Opus 4.7); DESIGN.md §4 polling cadence two-mode clarification (continuous loop + bl run --list); DESIGN.md §11.6 brief-render MD-canonical with HTML/PDF best-effort; PIVOT-v2.md §6.1 Sonnet 4.6 hunter dispatch demoted to Phase P3 roadmap (callable_agents)
[Change] M11 P7 — synthesize_defense wire-form + bl_defend_modsec --from-action consumption: schemas/defense.json adds reply-side fields (act_id, gate_status, staged_path, reason); src/bl.d/82-defend.sh consumes pending action JSON from memstore + jq-validates against schema; DESIGN.md + docs/case-layout.md actions/<state>/<act-id>.yaml → .json migration (closes DESIGN.md §12.2 spec-vs-build gap). Bonus: yara FP-gate flag -q → --no-warnings for yara 4.2.3/4.5.2 portability.
[Change] M11 P8 — reconstruct_intent wire-form + bl observe file --attribution-from consumption (schemas/intent.json gains attribution_id / layers_observed / observed_capability / dormant_capability reply-side fields; bl_observe_file fetches the curator-authored attribution payload from bl-case/<case>/attributions/<attr-id>.json memstore key, schema-validates, and embeds it in the file.triage record; closes DESIGN.md §12.3 spec-vs-build gap)
[New] M11 P5 — tests/03-models.bats: 8 tests covering Sonnet 4.6 bundle-summary routing (happy path + 401 fallback + --no-llm-summary + BL_DISABLE_LLM bypass) and Haiku 4.5 FP-gate adjudication (verdict:pass / verdict:match → 68 / malformed → 68 / BL_DISABLE_LLM bypass); 250/250 green on debian12 + rocky9
[New] M11 P13 — bl setup --sync delta-verification test: 3-skill fake repo, MANIFEST baseline shas captured pre-modify, modify foo/a.md, run bl setup --sync, assert exactly one memory POST for foo/a.md and zero for foo/{b,c}.md via per-invocation curl-shim request log (tests/helpers/curator-mock.bash gains BL_MOCK_REQUEST_LOG body-capture path). Closes audit gap "skills sync delta-detection asserted but never verified."

## 0.1.0 — 2026-04-26 — first public release

First shippable cut of blacklight — agent-directed defensive forensics CLI
built on the Managed Agents architecture. Single binary (`bl`), curl-pipe-
bash installer, RPM + DEB packages validated on debian12 / ubuntu2404 /
centos7 / rocky9. All motions (observe / consult / run / defend / clean /
case / setup / flush) land in this release.

[New] M10 P1 — install.sh curl-pipe-bash installer (bash≥4.1, curl, jq preflight; --local / remote modes; next-step prompt)
[New] M10 P2 — uninstall.sh (binary removal + interactive/--yes/--keep-state state handling; timestamped backup at /var/lib/bl.bk.<ts>/)
[New] M10 P4 — bl <verb> --help dispatch (per-verb help surfaces for observe/consult/run/defend/clean/case/setup/flush); tightened bl_usage; version-pin drift-guard
[New] M10 P5 — bl observe substrate verb (read-only host-substrate enumeration; 12 categories; <2s)
[New] M10 P6 — tests/10-install-paths.bats install roundtrip (8 BATS tests covering install.sh + uninstall.sh roundtrip)
[New] M10 P9 — pkg.manifest + pkg/ scaffold (RPM/DEB build infra via pkg_gen.sh; single-binary layout)
[New] M10 P10 — RPM build + install validation matrix (rocky9 + centos7)
[New] M10 P11 — skills bundle integration: 4 new namespaces × 18 files (ride-the-substrate/, legacy-os-pitfalls/, shared-hosting-attack-shapes/, agentic-minutes-playbook/); INDEX.md routing extended; skill count 46 → 65 (64 content files + INDEX.md)
[New] M10 P11 — DEB build + install validation matrix (debian12 + ubuntu2404)
[New] M10 P12 — .gitattributes pkg/ export-ignore + release-tarball audit
[Fix] M10 P13 — CentOS 6 floor recovery: portability fixes for bash 4.1
      (source-execute guard around set -euo pipefail; safe-expand for
      empty arrays under set -u), gawk 3.1.7 + Debian/Ubuntu mawk
      (literal-class regex replaces {N} interval quantifier in
      bl_fence_unwrap + bl_consult_find_open_case_by_fingerprint),
      coreutils 8.4 (ISO-8601 T-form normalized to space-form before
      date -d / find -newermt / touch -d), tr -d set ordering. Test
      lane 79 fail → 0; debian12 / rocky9 / centos6 all 228/228.
